-- French June New Car Sales Fell 1.2% as Government Incentives Phased Out
-- Vidya Root
-- 2010-07-01T10:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-01/french-new-car-sales-fall-12-in-may-ending-sequence-of-12-monthly-gains.html

          
          
             French new car sales fell 1.2 percent
in June as the government began phasing out incentives.  
 New car registrations fell to 240,587 units.  
 Light vehicle registrations, which include delivery trucks,
rose 0.9 percent to 283,554 units, led by a 29 percent increase
for Nissan Motor Ltd. and a 22 percent jump for General Motors
Co.  Renault SA  recorded a 0.6 percent gain in the month, while
Peugeot Citroen sales slid 2.7 percent.  
